WorldStage Newsonline — Five members of Boko Haram terrorists (BHTs) have met their waterloo as they along with others (BHTs) attempted woefully to ransack a military base at Buni yadi, in Gujba Local Government Area of Yobe State at about 06:05 hours (pm) on Saturday the 16th of February, 2019, according to a statement  by Colonel Sagir Musa, Acting Director Public Relations. The statement said an officer and  three soldiers have lost their lives during the encounter while five wounded soldiers were stable and receiving treatment in the Brigade Field Ambulance. “Though, the terrorists appeared prepared for the attack as they approached the military location with 4 gun trucks,1 Mine Resistant Ambush Protection,1 MOWAC and assorted arms and ammunitions, they, however, suffered heavy losses as five of the bandits/terrorists were effectively deleted, 9 x AK 47 rifles, 1x Anti Aircraft gun, 121 rounds of 12.7 mm Anti Aircraft ammunitions, 2x 36 hand grenades, 295 rounds of 7.62 mm special ammunition, 4x Improvised Explosive(IED) Device, 1x IED cylinder, 1x RPG bomb, 1x RPG bomb charger, 1x gun truck and 1x Bajaj Motorcycle were recovered,” the statement said. Meanwhile, the Chief of Army Staff Lieutenant General Tukur Yusuf Buratai was said to have commended in general terms, the successes being recorded by troops in recent times, in the various operational arenas especially in the North East and enjoined all personnel to remain resolute, alert and decisive as well as professional in the discharge of onerous national assignment.“Nigerian Army hereby expressed appreciation to all those who passed timely credible information that aided the successful abortion of this obviously deliberately  attempted attack on troops position in Buni Yadi,” the statement said. TROOPS NABS HOODLUMS SET TO DISRUPT ELECTIONS AT IWARAJA JUNCTIONIn another development, troops of Operation Safe Conduct deployed to provide security/conducive atmosphere for the conduct of a free, fair and credible Presidential/National Assembly Elections at Iwaraja Junction along Osun and Ogun axis on Saturday the 16th of February 2019 at about 0730hrs were said to have intercepted three hoodlums on motorcycle moving towards Ilesa East LGA to disrupt smooth conduct of 2019 general  elections in that area.A statement said the hoodlums were arrested and the items recovered from them include: 1× locally made pistol; 1× gutless; 3× rounds of cartridges; 3× mobile phones ; 1× iPad; 1× Peace Corps face cap; 1× Peace Corps ID card; And the sum of #14,300.It said those arrested will be handed over to the police upon completion of initial profiling and investigation.